<collectingCountry id="CCC4F3E073539712C3462C841AE7FA2E" box="[352,413,1455,1480]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="86A76F6273539712C3462C841AE7FA2E" bold="true" box="[352,413,1455,1480]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Male</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="2CE8AFF573539712C38A2C841A8CFA21" box="[428,502,1455,1480]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 − 8" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1604,1626]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1583]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 4 − 8. Callomyia males, lateral view. 4. C. argentea. 5. C. arnaudi (abdomen removed). 6. C. arnaudi abdomen in glycerin (coloured markings more metallic bluish-white than depicted). 7. C. browni. 8. C. bertae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271479/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2CE8AFF573539712C0252C9B1958FA2E" box="[515,546,1456,1480]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 − 18" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1892,1914]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,519,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,519,1870]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 15 − 18. Callomyia males, dorsal view. 15. C. argentea. 16. C. arnaudi (abdomen removed). 17. C. bertae. 18. C. browni." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271481/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">18</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="732B1E9573539712C0EF2C9B1859FA21" box="[713,803,1456,1480]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity id="732B1E9573539712C19A2C841F5EFA21" box="[956,1060,1455,1480]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" unit="mm" value="4.25">4.25 mm</quantity>
. Head brownish grey with silverblue reflections; face brownish-yellow ventrally; gena and postgena brown; mouthparts including palpus yellow; antenna with scape and pedicel brownish-yellow, first flagellomere and arista brown. Antenna with first flagellomere short-oval (as in 
<figureCitation id="2CE8AFF573539712C3CE2F301941F9D2" box="[488,571,1563,1588]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 − 44" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1512,1534]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,447,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,447,1490]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 41 − 44. Callomyia antennae. 41. C. calla, male antenna (first flagellomere short-oval). 42. C. gilloglyorum, male antenna (first flagellomere elongate-conical). 43. C. venusta, female antenna (first flagellomere short-oval). 44. C. gilloglyorum, female antenna (first flagellomere subtriangular)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271487/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
Fig. 
<number id="021BA15773539712C03A2F371941F9D2" box="[540,571,1564,1588]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B46CB37073539712C2E12F141FA9F979" blockId="17.[151,1437,1455,2020]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
Thorax black with silver-blue to silver-brown markings on postpronotal lobe, lateral portion of presutural scutum, notopleuron, postalar callus, propleuron, mesopleuron and metapleuron; posterior portion of postsutural scutum silver-blue; mediotergite and laterotergite silver-brown. Scutum with 
<number id="021BA15773539712C1DE2FAC1F7CF946" box="[1016,1030,1671,1696]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="6.0">6</number>
notopleural setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B46CB37073539712C2E12F8718C3F8D6" blockId="17.[151,1437,1455,2020]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
Legs pale yellow with fore and mid tarsomeres 
<number id="021BA15773539712C0C52F87198BF922" box="[739,753,1708,1732]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number id="021BA15773539712C10F2F80184DF922" box="[809,823,1707,1732]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="5.0">5</number>
yellowish-brown, hind leg darker with apex of femur, tibia and tarsomeres brown. Mid tibia with median anterodorsal seta absent, median dorsal seta present (as in 
<figureCitation id="2CE8AFF573539712C7562FE41BCDF8EA" captionStart="FIGURES 49 − 54" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 49 − 54. Callomyia legs. 49. C. proxima, male mid leg (with tibial setae). 50. C. velutina, male mid leg (with tibial seta). 51. C. proxima, female mid leg (with tibial seta). 52. C. velutina, female mid leg (with tibial seta). 53. C. argentea, male hind leg (with femoral seta). 54. C. corvina, male hind leg (with femoral seta). Abbreviations: ad s—anterodorsal seta; d sdorsal seta; pv s—posteroventral seta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271489/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
Fig. 
<number id="021BA15773539712C2B12FD81BCDF8EA" box="[151,183,1779,1804]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="50.0">50</number>
</figureCitation>
); base of hind femur with strong stout posteroventral seta (as in 
<figureCitation id="2CE8AFF573539712C1B02FD81890F8EA" box="[918,1002,1779,1804]" captionStart="FIGURES 49 − 54" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1704]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 49 − 54. Callomyia legs. 49. C. proxima, male mid leg (with tibial setae). 50. C. velutina, male mid leg (with tibial seta). 51. C. proxima, female mid leg (with tibial seta). 52. C. velutina, female mid leg (with tibial seta). 53. C. argentea, male hind leg (with femoral seta). 54. C. corvina, male hind leg (with femoral seta). Abbreviations: ad s—anterodorsal seta; d sdorsal seta; pv s—posteroventral seta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271489/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
Fig. 
<number id="021BA15773539712C1ED2FD81890F8EA" box="[971,1002,1779,1804]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry id="CCC4F3E073539712C6262FD81F42F8EA" box="[1024,1080,1779,1804]" name="India" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Hind</collectingCountry>
tarsomere 
<number id="021BA15773539712C6912FDF1FBFF8EA" box="[1207,1221,1780,1804]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="1.0">1</number>
expanded, slightly broader than apical width of hind tibia, length approximately 
<date id="C06D95B073539712C16E2E331810F8D6" box="[840,874,1816,1840]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
<number id="021BA15773539712C16E2E33182FF8D6" box="[840,853,1816,1840]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B46CB37073539712C2E12E101FF7F8B2" blockId="17.[151,1437,1455,2020]" box="[199,1165,1851,1876]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Wing hyaline with cell sc bluish-white. Halter lemon yellow with base of stem brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B46CB37073539712C2E12E7419B7F826" blockId="17.[151,1437,1455,2020]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
Abdomen with tergites 
<number id="021BA15773539712C3F42E4B1A87F89E" box="[466,509,1888,1912]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
entirely lemon yellow; tergite 
<number id="021BA15773539712C17B2E4B1811F89E" box="[861,875,1888,1912]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="4.0">4</number>
pale yellow, interrupted by median dorsal brown band extending posterolaterally; tergite 
<number id="021BA15773539712C0752EA8191BF87A" box="[595,609,1923,1948]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="5.0">5</number>
dark brown with anterolateral silver-blue marking; tergite 
<number id="021BA15773539712C6C92EA81F87F87A" box="[1263,1277,1923,1948]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="6.0">6</number>
and 
<number id="021BA15773539712C7142EAF1E3AF87D" box="[1330,1344,1924,1947]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="7.0">7</number>
entirely dark brown; sternites white, sternite 
<number id="021BA15773539712C0162E831944F826" box="[560,574,1960,1984]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" value="8.0">8</number>
pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B46CB37073539711C2E12EE01BACFE6E" blockId="17.[151,1437,1455,2020]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1437,151,680]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="519" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="2CE8AFF573539712C3682EE01ADEF802" box="[334,420,1995,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 55 − 58" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1837,1859]" captionTargetBox="[157,1435,312,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,303,1815]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 55 − 58. Callomyia male terminalia, lateral view. 55. C. argentea. 56. C. arnaudi. 57. C. bertae. 58. C. browni. Abbreviations: ap prj—apical projection; bv lb—basoventral lobe; cerc—cercus; d lb—dorsal lobe; d o csp—dorsal outer cusp; d prj—dorsal projection; epand—epandrium; epand ap proc—epandrial apical process; epand v lb—epandrial ventral lobe; hypd—hypandrium; hypd proc—hypandrial process; i proc—inner process; o proc—outer process; pgt—postgonite; phphallus; sur—surstylus; v i csp—ventral inner cusp; v prj—ventral projection; v proc—ventral process. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271490/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Figs 58</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2CE8AFF573539712C3892EE01AB6F802" box="[431,460,1995,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 63 − 69" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,614,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,589,1886]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 63 − 69. Callomyia male terminalia, lateral view (63 − 64); surstyli, posterior view (65 − 69). 63. C. velutina. 64. C. venusta. 65. C. argentea. 66. C. browni. 67. C. calla. 68. C. velutina. 69. C. venusta. Abbreviations: d o csp—dorsal outer cusp; v i csp—ventral inner cusp. Scale bar: Figs 63 − 64 = 0.1 mm; Figs 65 − 69 = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271492/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">66</figureCitation>
) with epandrium and hypandrium brown; surstylus dark brown; hypandrial process and cercus brownish-yellow. Epandrium with short broad ventral lobe, rounded at apex, slightly anteriorly directly; apical process moderately long, broad basally, pointed at apex. Surstylus molar-like, with 
<number id="021BA15773509711C6A629971FF4FF32" box="[1152,1166,188,212]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519" value="2.0">2</number>
large cusps very widely excavated in between; dorsal outer cusp broadly rounded in lateral view; ventral inner cusp rounded in lateral view, broadly truncate and minutely serrate medially in posterior view (
<figureCitation id="2CE8AFF573509711C1BA282F188EFEFB" box="[924,1012,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 63 − 69" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,614,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,589,1886]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 63 − 69. Callomyia male terminalia, lateral view (63 − 64); surstyli, posterior view (65 − 69). 63. C. velutina. 64. C. venusta. 65. C. argentea. 66. C. browni. 67. C. calla. 68. C. velutina. 69. C. venusta. Abbreviations: d o csp—dorsal outer cusp; v i csp—ventral inner cusp. Scale bar: Figs 63 − 64 = 0.1 mm; Figs 65 − 69 = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271492/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">
Fig. 
<number id="021BA15773509711C1F2282F188EFEFB" box="[980,1012,260,285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519" value="66.0">66</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium with moderately long apical process; process trifid, with 
<number id="021BA15773509711C00B28031941FEA6" box="[557,571,296,320]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519" value="2.0">2</number>
minute apical projections and small basoventral lobe. Postgonite long and widened toward apex, somewhat truncated and pointed at apex. 
<taxonomicName id="73D3C8F373509711C14D286718C7FE83" box="[875,957,332,357]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phallaceae" genus="Phallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Phallales" pageId="18" pageNumber="547" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Phallus</taxonomicName>
with sharp extended hook at apex. Cercus short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B46CB37073509711C2E128BF1AD8FE4B" blockId="18.[151,1437,151,680]" box="[199,418,404,429]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis id="86A76F6273509711C2E128BF1A64FE4B" bold="true" box="[199,286,404,429]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
